intense

in_tense

intense = 強烈的 / 高度集中的 / 非常激烈的


Intense (形容詞：強烈的、劇烈的)
Intense 用來形容壓力、情緒、熱度或競爭的「強度」很大。

1. 直接修飾 (放在名詞前)
I am under intense pressure at work. (我承受著巨大的工作壓力。)
The intense heat made me feel dizzy. (那股酷熱讓我感到頭暈。)

2. 間接修飾 (放在 be 動詞後)
The competition is intense. (競爭很激烈。)
The pain in my nose was intense after surgery. (手術後我鼻子的疼痛感很強烈。)




The pressure is intense.
The training was intense.
My focus is intense.



The heat today is intense.
The game was intense.
The training was intense 
The training was intense but useful.

He felt intense stress 
He felt intense stress at work.

She has intense feelings about her job.

We had an intense discussion 
We had an intense discussion in the meeting.




I have an intense schedule
I have an intense schedule this week." （我這週的行程非常緊湊。）
I have an intense workload
I have an intense workload today." （我今天的工作量非常大。）

I have an intense pain
I have an intense pain in my back." （我的背部有劇烈的疼痛。）
I have an intense feeling
I have an intense feeling that something is wrong." （我有一種強烈的直覺，覺得哪裡
